cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on facial expression synthesis, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel generative adversarial network (GAN) architecture, which falls under the subfield of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the second most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of facial geometry and fiducial points, which are related to computer graphics and geometry processing, respectively. Therefore, cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.GR (Computer Graphics), and cs.MM (Multimedia) are also likely sub-categories.
